author: dblevins
msg: The Evictor should stop draining the pool when it starts getting nulls.  It is more efficient for the strictPooling case. For the non-StrictPooling case it's the only way the Evictor would actually work and not drain infinitely.  Need to eventually add more non-strict tests.
